cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to attend relevant regions in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses RNN-based visual attention models, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of eye fixations labels also suggests the involvement of human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with video analysis, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques to learn to attend semantic regions in videos suggests the involvement of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
